			<td><br>Since 2004, David has driven company strategy and operations, cementing I-play™'s independent leadership position in Europe and the US, before its acquisition by Oberon Media, the world™'s leading casual games company in June 07.  Inspiring the concept of one thumb™ gaming to broaden the appeal of mobile games, launching the I-play brand and securing powerful strategic publishing relationships, Gosen has also delivered consistent revenue growth. 
Previously, Gosen served as MD of Nintendo, Europe driving significant growth and launching market-redefining platforms: GameCube and Game Boy Advance.  David launched Sky Digital at BSkyB, and served at Pepsico, Coca-Cola & Schweppes Beverages.</td>
